                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>convinced that the performance of some duties are<lb/> at times\n                                        neglected, and too often depend on the indul-<lb/>gence of\n                                        an All merciful Creator. Who knows<lb/> my heart and mind\n                                        with the will to perform all<lb/> duties; but however\n                                        mindful we may be of all<lb/> this tis harrowing to see or\n                                        hear of thousands<lb/> being summoned to the throne at one\n                                        moments<lb/> notice. May He in His infinite mercy guard us\n                                        all<lb/> and give us length of days for the full and\n                                        faithful<lb/> execution of His will. I trust my friend\n                                        that<lb/> my next will find me in spirits to give due<lb/>\n                                        attention to your favor.</p>\n                              <p>The sales also came to hand in good condition.<lb/> Love to all\n                                        friends and tell them they must not<lb/> be angry at my\n                                                  <sic>silense</sic> for the present.</p>\n                              <p>And now my kind friend that Heaven may<lb/> prosper your way and\n                                        lead you out of the<lb/> many snares which have been laid\n                                        for<lb/> you; guiding you in your <add>?</add> duty\n                                        which<lb/> you have so faithfully nurtured and bring\n                                        you<lb/> in the <add>?</add> of hearts capable of\n                                        appreciating<lb/> the true servant of the most High,\n                                        are<lb/> the wishes of your Friend and Pupil</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(4)\">\n                                        <persName role=\"author\">\n                                                  <hi rend=\"underline\">Simha</hi>\n                                                  <hi rend=\"underline\">C</hi>\n                                                  <hi rend=\"underline\">Peixotto</hi>\n                                        </persName>\n                              </p>\n                              <p>My dear Grandpa<add>?</add> joins<lb/> me in all the <add>?</add>\n                                        wishes<lb/> and hopes you will stand your<lb/> ground. We\n                                        have read the<lb/>\n                                        <sic>defence</sic>; and could add many<lb/> truths thereto\n                                        from many years<lb/> personal observation.</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p36970j2r/canvas/p2"
                }
              ]
